    dc:creator "Gustafsson, Daniel R.; Zou, Fasheng; Oslejskova, Lucie; Najer, Tomas; Sychra, Oldřich" ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "Four new species of Brueelia Kéler, 1936 (Phthiraptera: Ischnocera) from African hosts, with a redescription of Nirmus bicurvatus Piaget, 1880" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612939>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612947>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612955>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612949>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612951>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612953>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612941> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612939>
    dc:description "Figs 9–10. Brueelia semiscalaris sp. nov. ex Granatina granatina (Linnaeus, 1766). 9. ♂, holotype (NHML 1956-561), habitus, dorsal and ventral views. Antennae distorted in original, and not illustrated. 10. ♀, habitus, dorsal and ventral views." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2612939/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612947>
    dc:description "Figs 23–24. Brueelia terpsichore sp. nov. ex Euplectes jacksoni (Sharpe, 1891). 23. ♂, holotype (NHML 6084), habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 24. ♀, habitus, dorsal and ventral views." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2612947/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612955>
    dc:description "Figs 37–44. Habitus photos of the species of Brueelia described as new herein, showing overall pigmentation patterns. 37. B. pofadderensis sp. nov., ♀. 38. B. pofadderensis sp. nov., ♂. 39. B. semiscalaris sp. nov., ♀. 40. B. semiscalaris sp. nov., ♂. 41. B. terpsichore sp. nov., ♀. 42. B. terpsichore sp. nov., ♂. 43. B. sima sp. nov., ♀. 44. B. sima sp. nov., ♂. All photographs are to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2612955/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612949>
    dc:description "Figs 25–29. Brueelia terpsichore sp. nov. ex Euplectes jacksoni (Sharpe, 1891). 25–28. ♂, holotype (NHML 6084). 25. Head, dorsal and ventral views. 26. Genitalia, dorsal view. 27. Mesosome, ventral view. 28. Paramere, dorsal view. 29. ♀, subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2612949/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612951>
    dc:description "Figs 30–31. Brueelia sima sp. nov. ex Malimbus nitens (Gray, 1831). 30. ♂, holotype (NHML 1960- 295), habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 31. ♀, habitus, dorsal and ventral views." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2612951/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612953>
    dc:description "Figs 32–36. Brueelia sima sp. nov. ex Malimbus nitens (Gray, 1831). 32–35. ♂, holotype (NHML 1960-295). 32. Head, dorsal and ventral views. 33. Genitalia, dorsal view. 34. Mesosome, ventral view. 35. Paramere, dorsal view. 36. ♀, subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2612953/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612941>
    dc:description "Figs 11–15. Brueelia semiscalaris sp. nov. ex Granatina granatina (Linnaeus, 1766). 11–14. ♂, holotype (NHML 1956-561). 11. Head, dorsal and ventral views; a–b. Antennae from ♀, dorsal and ventral views. 12. Genitalia, dorsal view. 13. Mesosome, ventral view. 14. Paramere, dorsal view. 15. ♀, subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2612941/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

